    {
      "question": "If tangents $PA$ and $PB$ from a point $P$ to a circle with centre $O$ are inclined to each other at angle of $80^\\circ$, then find $\\angle POA$.",
      "answer": "$50^\\circ$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "In quadrilateral $OAPB$, $\\angle OAP = \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ$ (tangent property).",
          "Since $\\angle APB = 80^\\circ$, $\\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - 80^\\circ = 100^\\circ$.",
          "In $\triangle OPA$ and $\triangle OPB$, the line $OP$ bisects $\\angle AOB$ and $\\angle APB$.",
          "Therefore, $\\angle POA = \\frac{1}{2} \\angle AOB = \\frac{100^\\circ}{2} = 50^\\circ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - 80^\\circ = 100^\\circ \\\\ \\angle POA = \\frac{1}{2} \\angle AOB = 50^\\circ"
      },
